3205146 133313568 rs76475253 A T 36876.4 PASS 0 NaN NaN 507549 3.0103 0.0 NaN NaN 30.67 NaN 0.693 -6.275 DP

#### AC and AF = 0, means this variant was seen a total of 0 times, remove row #### Mapping quality = error in read alignment, Base quality = error in base calling #### MQ = root-mean-square of mapping quality of reads across samples. #### MQRankSum = difference in mapping quality between REF and ALT alleles (closer to 0 is better) #### Impute 0s for MQRankSum #### BaseQRankSum = different in base quality of REF vs ALT. Impute 0s #### ReadPosRankSum = relative positioning of REF versus ALT alleles within reads. Impute 0s #### Both InbreedingCoeff and ExcessHet measure consanguinuity #### SOR and FS measure strand bias. Impute FS with 0

drop collinear, constant, NaN features. drop features where a normalized alternative is present (eg. AF = AC/AN)¶

def filtered(s):
    if s == 'PASS':
        return 0
    else:
        return 1

df['Filtered'] = df['FILTER'].apply (lambda row: filtered(row))

Indels¶

In [72]:
def mutation_type(ref, alt):
    if len(ref) == len(alt):
        return "SNV"
    if len(ref) > len(alt):
        return "DEL"
    if len(ref) < len(alt):
        return "INS"
In [73]:
df['TYPE'] = df.apply(lambda x: mutation_type(x['REF'], x['ALT']), axis=1)
